Read this lovely excerpt by Paulo Coelho which I would like to share with you as it so beautifully illustrates “closing cycles”..

Did you lose your job? Has a loving relationship come to an end? Did you leave your parents’ house? Gone to live abroad? Has a long-lasting friendship ended all of a sudden?
You can spend a long time wondering why this has happened.

Things pass, and the best we can do is to let them really go away.

Everything in this visible world is a manifestation of the invisible world, of what is going on in our hearts – and getting (materially) rid of certain memories also means making some room for other memories to take their place.

Let things go. Release them. Detach yourself from them.

Stop turning on your emotional television to watch the same program over and over again, the one that shows how much you suffered from a certain loss: that is only poisoning you, nothing else.

Before a new chapter is begun, the old one has to be finished: tell yourself that what has passed will never come back.

Remember that there was a time when you could live without that thing or that person – nothing is irreplaceable, a habit is not a need.

This may sound so obvious, it may even be difficult, but it is very important.

Closing cycles. Not because of pride, incapacity or arrogance, but simply because that no longer fits your life.
Stop being “who you were,” and change into “who you are.”❣️❣️

A lifetime is not enough to  express the depth of love @pareishani and I have for #NewYork. This is a mere attempt to capture how we feel every time someone mentions ‘New York’! ❤️💙 

Oh, New York, vibrant and bold,
A city of dreams, stories untold.
With towering skyscrapers that touch the sky,
You captivate all who pass you by.

In your streets, a symphony of sounds,
A melting pot of cultures that astounds.
From Manhattan to Brooklyn, the Bronx to Queens,
A kaleidoscope of life bursting at the seams.

From Times Square’s dazzling lights,
To Central Park’s serene delights,
The energy flows through every block,
An electric pulse that cannot be locked.

From the Statue of Liberty, a beacon of hope,
To the Empire State, standing tall with scope,
You’ve weathered storms and risen above,
A resilient spirit, an enduring love.

From Wall Street’s suits to bohemian cafes,
Your diversity weaves through each passing phase.
A city of dreams, where anything can be,
In the heart of you, I find my glee.

Oh, New York, you’re a tapestry divine,
A haven for dreamers, a place to shine.
Your spirit, like a flame, forever burns,
In the hearts of those whose love for you yearns.

So here’s to you, New York, my ode to thee,
A city of dreams, where I long to be.
In your embrace, I find solace and light,
New York City, forever shining bright.
.
.
.
.

#TFNExclusive : Say Hello to Cray Craft @craycraftmumbai , the newest gem among the plethora of amazing restaurants in Andheri. This place boasts a beautiful ambience, complemented by a menu filled with meticulously crafted dishes and innovative cocktails. 

The ‘Cray’ in their name stands for Crazy Cocktails, while The ‘Craft’ stands for Craft Cuisine - presented in an elegant fine-dine setting, featuring Modern Indian delicacies that are sure to captivate your taste buds. Cray Craft brings together the best of both worlds, offering crazy cocktails, crafty cuisine, and an impeccable dance vibe, all conveniently housed under one roof. 

When you visit, be sure to indulge in their must-try delights, such as the Crab/Chicken 65 Croquette, Lal Maas Bao, Carrot Rasam, and the tantalizing cocktails like the Piggy Jack, Butterfly Blue Pea Mogra, and Popcorn Tiki. And don’t you dare leave without savoring their absolutely delightful dark chocolate mouse and Crème Brûlée . So come and immerse yourself in this one-of-a-kind culinary journey. 

📍 Town Centre, Andheri - Kurla Rd, Mittal Industrial Estate, Marol, Andheri East

For reservations, call 9920062479☎️

Ode to my maternal #Grandfather, Mr Kashinath Mitra on his 104th Birthday!

Born on August's eleventh morn, in 1919's embrace,
From royal roots, a legacy woven with grace.
A life well-lived, a tapestry spun,
A journey through time, a story begun.

Retired Assistant collector of customs, a title of pride,
On the field, East Bengal's jersey he'd stride.
A painter, an artist, his creativity soared,
Colors and canvases, his spirit explored.

A father, a grandfather, love's endless sea,
His heart's embrace, a sanctuary to be.
The kindest soul, a heart of gold,
In his love's warmth, young and old.

And now, as years have gracefully passed,
His memory lingers, an echo steadfast.
In stories recounted, and laughter's embrace,
In the kindness he’d show, in every trace.

Handsome in spirit, in love he’s thrive 
In memories cherished, he continues to survive.
As we celebrate his life…I’m sure from above,
He’s watching, protecting, his legacy of love..❤️❤️

#NewRestaurantAlert: From the folks behind @blabberallday comes a new Bali-Inspired restaurant in Mumbai. #Baliboo in Goregaon carries Bali-inspired aesthetics with pastel prints, soft lighting, and high ceilings add to the tropical feel. 

While the interiors—play off muted and minimal tones, the menu is anything but. At @baliboo.official, diners can enjoy a variety of Asian, Indian and fusion delicacies. We tried the Mustard Fish Tikka, Crispy Lamb Stir Fry, Chettinad Prawns, Crispy Lotus Stem, Shitake Mushroom Croquettes, California Rolls and Black Pepper Paneer with Edamame Fried Rice. Each dish was perfectly executed and delicious. 

Baliboo serves up cocktails - and serves them well. There’s a range of gin-based, whisky-based and rum-based cocktails, infused with citrus, and other distinct flavours.  But what we especially appreciated was their unique choice of mocktails, some of which had unusual flavour combinations.  Whether it’s a group outing with friends, a cosy date or a family gathering, this new cafe and bar can be a great choice.

Address:  First Floor, Commerz II, International Business Park, Oberoi Garden City, off Western Express Highway, Yashodham, Goregaon, Mumbai, Maharashtra 400063

#NewRestaurantAlert | Almost everyone has heard of Paul Bakery & Restaurant, an eatery which began as a humble bakery in France in 1889. With outlets in over 30 countries Paul just debuted its first outlet in Mumbai. Paul is known for its baked goods, which are freshly prepared each day, the smells of which waft around the vicinity, luring you in for a bite to eat. From breakfast to burgers, fresh salads to healthy grills and creamy pastas to creative desserts, coffee, and milkshakes, you can order it all at the Parisian-inspired venue, pick it out fresh from the deli to take away, or even test out the home delivery service – whichever way you choose to do it, Paul never disappoints.

They say Route 66, that iconic 2,400-mile stretch from #Chicago to #SantaMonica, is a journey back in time—an era of neon signs and charming diners. But #Route66 is more than just a road; it's a tapestry of history woven into the fabric of America. An artery of transport, a catalyst for social change, and a remnant of America’s past, connecting two-thirds of the continent.

On #worldtourismday it’s a flashback to 2019, when I embarked on a month-long #americanodyssey through 9 states, indulging in my passion to explore the five iconic National Parks: #GrandTeton, #Yellowstone, #BryceCanyon, #Zion, and the #GrandCanyon. @visit_arizona 

This shot was taken en route to Williams, Arizona—the gateway to the Grand Canyon. The spirit of Route 66 runs deep in Williams. Classic cars line the streets, old-fashioned street lamps illuminate the way, and unique shops brim with Route 66 memorabilia. The atmosphere alone is a portal to the golden age of the Mother Road. 

Catch more glimpses of Williams in my stories. And in the weeks ahead, brace yourselves for a photo dump from my National Parks adventure—a testament to the need to preserve these natural treasures. 
.
.
.
.

#Flashback2019 | Caught between the dance of sunlight and shadow, the ethereal beauty of #AntelopeCanyon leaves one breathless. Located in the heart of the American Southwest, Antelope Canyon is a captivating geological marvel, carved into the Navajo sandstone, a sedimentary rock formation characterized by its vibrant red and orange colors that dates back to the Jurassic period. This iconic slot canyon, known for its wave-like structures and the beams of sunlight that shine down from openings in the top, serves as a breathtaking testament to nature's artistry and time's passage.

#Flashback2019 | Yes, Thor's Hammer is a genuine geological formation situated in Bryce Canyon National Park, Utah. This striking feature is a prime representation of a unique rock structure known as a hoodoo, commonly found in dry basins and badlands. Bryce Canyon is home to countless such hoodoos. Often referred to as fairy chimneys or earth pyramids, these formations can be likened to totem poles, towering spires, or nature's own skyscrapers.

#ChristmasSpecial | St. Patrick’s Cathedral, an iconic New York house of worship, has welcomed visitors since 1879. Located on Fifth Avenue, across from Rockefeller Center, the church is the largest Gothic Catholic cathedral in the US. This landmark, dedicated in 1879, attracts over five million visitors annually. Featuring 330-foot spires, it stands out as one of the City’s most spectacular architectural sights. Internally, it accommodates 2,400 with numerous altars, stained glass windows, and a grand organ boasting 7,855 pipes. Thousands flock to  St. Patrick’s Cathedral for the Christmas Eve Mass. For those unable to attend in person, the experience can be enjoyed in real-time through the church’s website and their YouTube channel. @stpatrickscathedral .
.
